Feature: Data Loading # features/01_data_loading.feature:3
  As a GCO application
  I need to load data from various sources
  So that the dashboard displays accurate information
  Scenario: Load scores data                       # features/01_data_loading.feature:8
    Given the data directory exists                # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:27
    When I load the scores data                    # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:35
    Then I should get a pandas DataFrame           # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:42
    And the DataFrame should have required columns # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:48

  Scenario: Load events data                   # features/01_data_loading.feature:14
    Given the data directory exists            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:27
    When I load the events data                # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:56
    Then events should be a list               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:63
    And each event should have required fields # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:69

  Scenario: Load announcements data                   # features/01_data_loading.feature:20
    Given the data directory exists                   # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:27
    When I load the announcements data                # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:78
    Then announcements should be a list               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:85
    And each announcement should have required fields # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:91

  Scenario: Load cup data                # features/01_data_loading.feature:26
    Given the data directory exists      # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:27
    When I load the cup data             # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:100
    Then cup data should be a dictionary # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:107
    And cup data should have draw key    # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:113

  Scenario: Load outing data                 # features/01_data_loading.feature:32
    Given the data directory exists          # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:27
    When I load the outing data              # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:119
    Then outing data should be a dictionary  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:126
    And outing data should have red_team key # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:132

Feature: Data Export/Import # features/02_data_export_import.feature:3
  As an admin user
  I need to export and import application state
  So that I can backup and restore data
  Scenario: Export application state                       # features/02_data_export_import.feature:8
    Given the data is loaded                               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:140
    When I export the app state                            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:150
    Then I should get a dictionary with all data sections  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:156
    And the dictionary should have version and export_date # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:164

  Scenario: Import valid backup            # features/02_data_export_import.feature:14
    Given I have a valid backup JSON       # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:171
    When I import the backup               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:185
    Then all data sections should be saved # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:196

  Scenario: Save backup to file                                  # features/02_data_export_import.feature:19
    Given I have application state                               # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:202
    When I save to backup                                        # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:208
    Then a backup file should be created in the backup directory # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:218

Feature: Backup Management # features/03_backup_management.feature:3
  As a system admin
  I need to manage backup files
  So that I can restore previous states
  Scenario: List available backups                     # features/03_backup_management.feature:8
    Given backup files exist in the backup directory   # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:227
    When I list the backups                            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:238
    Then I should get a list of backups sorted by date # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:244

  Scenario: Compute diff between backup and current    # features/03_backup_management.feature:13
    Given I have a backup and current state            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:250
    When I compute the diff                            # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:259
    Then I should get a dictionary showing differences # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:265

Feature: Player Management # features/04_player_management.feature:3
  As a league administrator
  I need to manage player information
  So that the league operates correctly
  Scenario: Load player list     # features/04_player_management.feature:8
    Given the club has players   # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:273
    When I load the player list  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:279
    Then I should get 13 players # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:285

  Scenario: Verify team assignments      # features/04_player_management.feature:13
    Given players are assigned to teams  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:291
    When I check team assignments        # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:298
    Then Red Team should have 6 players  # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:305
    And Black Team should have 7 players # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:311

Feature: Tournament Management # features/05_tournament_management.feature:3
  As a league administrator
  I need to manage tournament data
  So that tournament results are displayed correctly
  Scenario: Verify league tournaments exist      # features/05_tournament_management.feature:8
    Given tournaments are defined                # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:319
    When I check league tournaments              # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:325
    Then there should be at least one tournament # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:331

  Scenario: Verify outing matches exist   # features/05_tournament_management.feature:13
    Given outing matches are defined      # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:337
    When I check outing matches           # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:343
    Then there should be 4 outing matches # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:349

Feature: Data Validation # features/06_data_validation.feature:3
  As a data integrity system
  I need to validate data structures
  So that the application doesn't crash on invalid data
  Scenario: Scores DataFrame structure                                                                                                               # features/06_data_validation.feature:8
    Given scores data is loaded                                                                                                                      # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:357
    When I validate the DataFrame structure                                                                                                          # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:363
    Then it should have required columns: Player, Tournament, Game, Net_Score, Gross_Score, Birdies, Pars, Bogeys, Double_Bogeys, Eagles, Stableford # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:369

  Scenario: Events have required fields            # features/06_data_validation.feature:13
    Given events are loaded                        # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:377
    When I validate an event                       # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:383
    Then it should have: date, name, type, details # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:392

  Scenario: Announcements have required fields                         # features/06_data_validation.feature:18
    Given announcements are loaded                                     # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:408
    When I validate announcement structure                             # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:414
    Then announcement should have id, title, date, author, body fields # features/steps/data_layer_steps.py:400

